Class Program

  • java.lang.Object
    • Program

  • public class Program
extends java.lang.Object
    This program is run in conjunction with two classes, ToyRobot and Table. This class contains the main method which executes the simulated Toy Robot on a Table game.

    This game allows the user to place the Toy Robot on the Table at any time, move the Toy Robot forward, turn the Toy Robot 90 degrees either left or right, and report its current position. The Toy Robot will start off without being placed on the table and will ignore all commands except valid "PLACE" and "EXIT" commands.

    The game will stop the Toy Robot from falling off the edges of the Table and the user can exit the game at any stage.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Lee Manuele

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        This is the main method where program execution begins.

        The program accepts commands from the user, validates them and decides to either act on valid commands or ignore invalid commands. The program also decides to act on or ignore commands depending on the state of the ToyRobot.
